(1) On the coming into force of this Act, the Children Act, 1974 (Act No. XXXIX of 1974), hereinafter referred to as the said Act, shall be repealed.

(2) Notwithstanding the repeal under sub-section (1), under the said Act-

(a) any act done or action taken shall be deemed to have been done or taken under this Act;

(b) The works pending on the date of the coming into force of this Act shall, as far as possible, be completed in accordance with the provisions of this Act;

(c) The status of the child residing in a certified institute or remand home in continuation of the pending case shall continue in the same manner as before in accordance with the provisions of this Act;

(d) The pending cases filed in the juvenile courts, which are pending, shall be disposed of through the said juvenile courts in such a manner as if the said Act had not been repealed and abolished;

(e) All other institutions including established youth development centres, youth development centres or residences, by whatever name they are established, shall, until further orders, continue their activities as if they had been established or certified under this Act;

(f) If a child disobeying his parents is detained in a child development center or certified institution and they remain in detention, they shall be returned to their parents or guardians immediately after the period for which they have been detained has expired.

(1) For the purpose of carrying out the purposes of this Act, a committee called the 'Upazila Committee on the Rights and Protection of Persons with Disabilities' shall be formed in every Upazila, consisting of the following members, namely:

(a) The Upazila Executive Officer, who shall also be its President;

(b) Upazila Health and Family Planning Officer;

(c) Upazila Engineer of the Local Government Engineering Department;

(d) Officer-in-charge of the police station;

(e) Upazila Secondary Education Officer;

(f) Upazila Education Officer;

(g) Upazila Women's Affairs Officer;

(h) Chairman of the Upazila Legal Aid Committee;

(i) a representative nominated by the Mayor of the Municipality, if any;

(j) A person engaged in social service work in the concerned Upazila nominated by the Upazila Executive Officer;

(j) Not more than 2 (two) representatives, including 1 (one) woman, nominated by the Upazila Executive Officer from a non-governmental organization working to protect the rights of persons with disabilities or an organization of persons with disabilities or a self-help organization;

(k) Upazila Social Service Officer, who shall also be its Member Secretary.

(2) The Chairman of the Upazila Parishad shall be the advisor to the committee mentioned in sub-section (1).

(3) The Upazila Committee shall carry out its responsibilities and activities within the territorial limits of the entire Upazila except the urban area, if any, within the concerned Upazila and if there is no existing Urban Social Services (UCD) office of the Social Services Department in any Municipality within the Upazila, the Upazila Committee shall carry out its responsibilities and activities in that Municipality as well.

