(i) Providing guidance to those concerned in formulating policies, planning and implementing plans related to reintegration and rehabilitation into family and social life;

(ii) To determine their gender-based numbers and collect information and data on their lifestyles for the purpose of welfare and development and to provide necessary advice to the government in this regard;

(e) to determine, where applicable, the necessary alternative approach or alternative means of care and to review the information and data of the child covered by such approach or care;

